OL,6,FHe spent two months in intensive care
OL,7,Fat Birmingham Children's Hospital,
OL,8,Fhaving lost half of his tongue due to
OL,9,Fthe toxic substance.
OL,11,FHe could not eat and initially had to
OL,12,Fbe fed through his nose.JDoctors said
OL,13,Fthey had never seen such a severe case
OL,14,Fin someone so young, with it being "a
OL,15,Fmillion-to-one he survived".
OL,17,FSam, now aged 18 months, is back home,
OL,18,Fbut he is being fed through his
OL,19,Fstomach.
